		"description": "<p>You practically hum with the divine power coursing through your veins. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Constitution, Intelligence, or Charisma increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>When casting a cleric spell with a costly material component, you may spend hit dice instead of the costly material component at a conversion rate of 1 hit die per 50gp of material cost. You must cover the entire cost of the material component you spend hit dice on this way to use this benefit, but if a spell has multiple material components with itemized costs, you can choose to use this benefit for some, but not all, of the components. Once you have spent a number of hit dice equal to your proficiency bonus this way, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest in a haven.</li>\n<li>When wielding your favored weapon, your cleric levels count as bloodblade levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e-bloody-heretics.bloody-heretics.Item.RMftoqexXdu7NKbN]{Igniting Reach} feature.</li>\n<li>Half your bloodblade levels count as cleric levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.2jlxytgjvgjnafvr]{Providence} feature.</li>\n<li>If you are reduced to 0 hit points, you begin with a successful death save.</li>\n<li>When you spend one or more hit dice to heal yourself, choose a friendly creature within 30 feet. That creature recovers hit points equal to half the number you recovered from your hit dice. Once you have used this benefit, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest.</li>\n</ul>",
